<h1>How it works</h1>
<p>
  As Open Meeting is made for simplicity, so it has basic unbreakable rules
  used across the system.
</p>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="feature-comparison <% if !auth_valid? %>n<% end %>auth">
  <tr>
    <th>Feature</th>
    <th>Anonymous users</th>
    <th>Invitee or attendee</th>
    <th>Authenticated users</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Set up and organize meetings</td>
    <td>No</td>
    <td>No</td>
    <td>Yes</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Change the information of a particular meeting</td>
    <td>No</td>
    <td>No</td>
    <td>Yes (1)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>View the information of public meetings</td>
    <td>Yes</td>
    <td>Yes</td>
    <td>Yes</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>View the information of protected meetings</td>
    <td>Yes (2)</td>
    <td>Yes</td>
    <td>Yes (1)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Invite people to join a public meeting</td>
    <td>Yes (3)</td>
    <td>Yes (3)</td>
    <td>Yes (1)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Invite people to join a protected meeting</td>
    <td>No</td>
    <td>Yes (3)</td>
    <td>Yes (1)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Revoke the invitation from invitees or attendees</td>
    <td>No</td>
    <td>No</td>
    <td>Yes (1)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Respond to meetings</td>
    <td>No</td>
    <td>Yes</td>
    <td>No (4)</td>
  </tr>
