<p>
  The numbers used in the table above stands for the following conditions.
</p>
<ol>
  <li>If the user owns the meeting.</li>
  <li>If the user is authorized to access the protected data or the data is public.</li>
  <li>If the meeting is open for registration or everyone is allowed to participate.</li>
  <li>
    The meeting organizer is assumed to attend the meeting. Inviting yourself
    does not mean the invitation ties to your account. It is possible to do but
    it is a good practice not to invite yourself.
  </li>
  <li>Only the participant can edit his own note.</li>
</ol>